129    /**
130    * An axis for displaying numerical data.
131    * <P>
132    * If the axis is set up to automatically determine its range to fit the data,
133    * you can ensure that the range includes zero (statisticians usually prefer
134    * this) by setting the <code>autoRangeIncludesZero</code> flag to
135    * <code>true</code>.
136    * <P>
137    * The <code>NumberAxis</code> class has a mechanism for automatically
138    * selecting a tick unit that is appropriate for the current axis range. This
139    * mechanism is an adaptation of code suggested by Laurence Vanhelsuwe.
140    */
